WEBVTT

00:00:08.475 --> 00:00:10.143
My name is Duncan Dixon.

00:00:10.143 --> 00:00:13.146
I'm the technology teacher
at Marshview Middle School.

00:00:13.780 --> 00:00:16.983
What I'm here to talk about today
is that is how I bring my personal

00:00:16.983 --> 00:00:20.086
passions, into my workplace
and into my classroom and

00:00:20.387 --> 00:00:25.058
and in front of my students and,
I have some odd passions that I would say

00:00:25.058 --> 00:00:28.028
that they're outside of the norm,
but I really like disc golf.

00:00:28.028 --> 00:00:30.630
And I do do that
with an engaged group of students.

00:00:30.630 --> 00:00:32.265
I've taught disc golf several times.

00:00:32.265 --> 00:00:33.933
And air cooled Volkswagens.

00:00:33.933 --> 00:00:38.905
I've been obsessed with them for 40
years, and, I can't get enough of it, so.

00:00:39.172 --> 00:00:42.509
And that's the particular example that,
I want to talk to you about today.

00:00:42.542 --> 00:00:46.446
It's just I had a student in my class
that that doesn't read.

00:00:46.579 --> 00:00:49.849
And I don't teach. I don't teach English.

00:00:50.150 --> 00:00:52.652
I'm just teaching technology,
but he's in my homeroom class

00:00:52.652 --> 00:00:56.389
and in my advisory class, and,
we had done a literacy,

00:00:56.489 --> 00:01:00.760
block and advisory,
and I just noticed that he never read.

00:01:00.760 --> 00:01:02.395
He fake read really well.

00:01:02.395 --> 00:01:06.266
But he had no no interest, no ability,

00:01:06.266 --> 00:01:10.270
no passion for reading, and just didn't
really see anything for him.

00:01:11.371 --> 00:01:12.739
But he's a hands on.

00:01:12.739 --> 00:01:13.973
Guys have my tech class.

00:01:13.973 --> 00:01:16.276
He likes to build stuff
he likes, takes off apart.

00:01:16.276 --> 00:01:18.878
So I thought, hey, what about Volkswagens?

00:01:18.878 --> 00:01:20.747
I love Volkswagens that I can show.

00:01:20.747 --> 00:01:22.515
You know, share my passion with him.

00:01:22.515 --> 00:01:25.351
So I brought in a book, written
by Prescott Phillips,

00:01:25.351 --> 00:01:28.354
and suggested
how to rebuild an air cooled motor.

00:01:28.655 --> 00:01:31.124
And it's really easy to rebuild
an air cooled motor.

00:01:31.124 --> 00:01:32.759
You don't have to be a mechanic.
You don't do anything.

00:01:32.759 --> 00:01:34.394
You just have to follow the steps.

00:01:34.394 --> 00:01:37.097
So I bought him in this book
and introduced it to him

00:01:37.097 --> 00:01:41.067
and said, hey, maybe you could read this,
you know, or just start looking at this

00:01:41.067 --> 00:01:43.236
at least has lots of pictures in it,
you know?

00:01:43.236 --> 00:01:45.105
But it does
have a lot of technical language

00:01:45.105 --> 00:01:47.107
that he would have to figure out
and look up and things like that.

00:01:47.107 --> 00:01:49.876
So a great introduction into reading.

00:01:49.876 --> 00:01:51.711
If you're not passionate about reading.

00:01:51.711 --> 00:01:54.647
We got permission from a XLA teacher
that that could be his book

00:01:54.647 --> 00:01:56.683
for the major project
that they were doing this year,

00:01:56.683 --> 00:02:00.053
which was lit on,
basically a science fair for books.

00:02:00.720 --> 00:02:03.556
And he was really nervous about it
because he had never read a book,

00:02:03.556 --> 00:02:06.993
you know, had and didn't really have
any plans on reading one at this point.

00:02:07.160 --> 00:02:09.095
But he really enjoyed this book.

00:02:09.095 --> 00:02:12.765
So we started just by him, you know,
scanning through it, looking through it,

00:02:12.765 --> 00:02:15.869
looking at the pictures, seeing what,
you know, what was it was all about.

00:02:16.202 --> 00:02:18.705
And then creating things
like the list of tools,

00:02:18.705 --> 00:02:20.473
because there's a whole
first chapter is just

00:02:20.473 --> 00:02:22.876
these are the tools
you need, in order to do this.

00:02:22.876 --> 00:02:27.180
So he created his own personal list,
and I told him if he got into it enough

00:02:27.180 --> 00:02:29.249
that maybe I could bring in a motor
next year and,

00:02:29.249 --> 00:02:31.317
you know, for an engage project
or something, a bunch of us

00:02:31.317 --> 00:02:33.553
could try to rebuild this motor.

00:02:33.553 --> 00:02:36.156
And he that excited him
a little bit more even, you know,

00:02:36.156 --> 00:02:37.690
but I said he'd have to read the book
first.

00:02:37.690 --> 00:02:40.026
You know, it's no good to me
if he hasn't read the book.

00:02:40.026 --> 00:02:42.295
So, And then he started reading the book.

00:02:42.295 --> 00:02:45.498
And I
would bring in other Volkswagen books

00:02:45.498 --> 00:02:48.601
because of course, being a Volkswagen
fanatic, I have 50 Volkswagen books.

00:02:49.235 --> 00:02:52.639
I would just bring them in when we were
doing a reading block and advisory,

00:02:52.639 --> 00:02:55.942
and I'd read that one
and he'd come over and see that book

00:02:56.242 --> 00:02:59.045
and realize, hey, there's
more than one of these type of books.

00:02:59.045 --> 00:03:00.280
And he'd, you know, flip through

00:03:00.280 --> 00:03:02.115
and he find little bits and read it and,

00:03:02.115 --> 00:03:04.284
you know,
showed a lot of interest in them.

00:03:04.284 --> 00:03:07.053
So he's you know, he's looking at it
saying, hey, there's lots of books

00:03:07.053 --> 00:03:08.521
